Sentencas: Potential interconnect alloys of Fe-Cr and Fe-Ni-Cr were fabricated via extrusion of metal oxide pastes followed by heat treatment in hydrogen.
Titulo: Thermal expansion matching and oxidation resistance of Fe-Ni-Cr interconnect alloys

Sentencas: Thermal expansion of the different alloys was measured and compared with that of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ).
Titulo: Thermal expansion matching and oxidation resistance of Fe-Ni-Cr interconnect alloys

Sentencas: Oxidation experiments were performed in air at 700 degrees C using cyclic heating and weighing, as well as thermogravimetric analysis.
Titulo: Thermal expansion matching and oxidation resistance of Fe-Ni-Cr interconnect alloys

Sentencas: Additions of chromium to a Fe50Ni alloy were found to improve oxidation resistance although the performance of Fe-Ni-Cr compositions was inferior to Fe-Cr alloys of similar chromium content.
Titulo: Thermal expansion matching and oxidation resistance of Fe-Ni-Cr interconnect alloys

Sentencas: The improvement in oxidation behavior with increasing chromium content of the Fe-Ni-Cr alloys was contrasted with the negative impact of the chromium addition on thermal expansion matching with YSZ.
Titulo: Thermal expansion matching and oxidation resistance of Fe-Ni-Cr interconnect alloys

Sentencas: Binary Fe-Cr alloys such as Fe20Cr appear to be better suited for use as a SOFC interconnect compared with Fe42.5Ni15Cr and other similar Fe-Ni-Cr alloys.
Titulo: Thermal expansion matching and oxidation resistance of Fe-Ni-Cr interconnect alloys
